Stimulus Specification:
# Stimulus Function: draw_linear_graph_line_only
{
  "point1_x": {"type": "int", "value": 0, "fixed": true, "description": "Must be 0 (y-intercept point)"},
  "point1_y": {"type": "int", "range": [-8, 8], "description": "y-intercept value (b in y = mx + b)"},
  "point2_x": {"type": "int", "range": [-8, 8], "exclude": [0], "description": "x-coordinate of second lattice point"},
  "point2_y": {"type": "int", "range": [-8, 8], "description": "y-coordinate of second lattice point"},
  "grid_range": {"type": "int", "value": 10, "optional": true, "description": "Axis range ±grid_range"},
  "line_color": {"type": "string", "value": "#1a6fb5", "optional": true, "description": "Line color hex"},
  "show_grid": {"type": "boolean", "value": true, "optional": true, "description": "Show gridlines"}
}

GENERATION CONSTRAINTS:
- point1_x is always 0 (the y-intercept point)
- point2_x != 0 (points must be different and no vertical lines)
- Slope = (point2_y - point1_y) / (point2_x - point1_x) must be:
    - An integer (e.g., 2, -3, 4): set point2_x so that (point2_y - point1_y) is divisible by point2_x
    - OR a unit fraction 1/n where n is single-digit: set point2_y - point1_y = ±1, point2_x = ±n
- Both points must have all coordinates within ±8 (visual clarity within grid_range=10)
- No horizontal lines (point1_y != point2_y)

EXAMPLE INSTANCES:
Integer slope (m = 4):    {"point1_x": 0, "point1_y": -7, "point2_x": 1, "point2_y": -3}
Unit fraction (m = 1/4):  {"point1_x": 0, "point1_y": -2, "point2_x": 4, "point2_y": -1}
Negative slope (m = -2):  {"point1_x": 0, "point1_y": 5, "point2_x": 2, "point2_y": 1}
Neg fraction (m = -1/3):  {"point1_x": 0, "point1_y": 4, "point2_x": 3, "point2_y": 3}

