Stimulus Type Description
Example:
{
    "line_min": 0,
    "line_max": 8,
    "points": [
        {
            "value": 1.0,
            "label": "$\\frac{\\sqrt{9}}{3}$"
        },
        {
            "value": 6.283185307,
            "label": "$2\\pi$"
        }
    ]
}

And the general structure:

{
    "line_min": "<left endpoint of visible line (float, not labeled)>",
    "line_max": "<right endpoint of visible line (float, not labeled)>",
    "points": [
        {
            "value": "<numeric position on the line (float)>",
            "label": "<display label, supports LaTeX math e.g. '$\\frac{\\sqrt{9}}{3}$', '$2\\pi$', '1.5'>"
        }
    ]
}

Key notes:

value is the actual numeric position (e.g. 1.0 for √9/3, 6.283... for 2π)
label is what's displayed above the tick -- supports LaTeX math with $...$ delimiters
line_min/line_max set the visible range; all point values must fall within this range
Arrows are drawn automatically at both ends
Tick marks appear only at the specified points (no intermediate ticks)
1-10 points supported

