Stimulus Type Description for draw_identity_function_all_graph_WE (Vertical Line Test — OpenAI-compatible)

The draw_identity_function_all_graph_WE function is an OpenAI-compatible variant of draw_identity_functions_graph_WE. It produces two images from the same graph configuration:

1. Original graph — identical to draw_identity_functions with display_type="graph"
2. Vertical line test overlay — the same graph with dashed vertical line(s) and coloured dots at intersection points

The visual output is identical to draw_identity_functions_graph_WE. The only difference is the schema: all coordinate pairs use [x, y] lists (with min/max length 2) instead of (x, y) tuples, so the generated JSON Schema emits "items" instead of "prefixItems" — making it safe for OpenAI's structured-output / function-calling API.

Required Format
{
    "graph_desc": {
        "display_type": "graph",
        "graph_shape": "points|circle|ellipse|curve|lines",
        // ... shape-specific fields (see sections below)
    },
    "vertical_lines": [
        {
            "x": <x-coordinate>,
            "intersection_points": [[x1, y1], [x2, y2], ...]
        }
    ],
    "vline_color": "#E91E63"
}

Note: Every coordinate pair is a 2-element list [x, y], not a tuple.


Section 1: Solid Shapes (graph_shape="points")

Example 1 — Solid Triangle (NOT a function)

{
    "graph_desc": {
        "display_type": "graph",
        "graph_shape": "points",
        "pairs": [[0, 3], [-3, -2], [3, -2]],
        "closed_shape": true,
        "fill_shape": true,
        "x_label": "x",
        "y_label": "y",
        "show_grid": true,
        "title": null
    },
    "vertical_lines": [
        {
            "x": 0,
            "intersection_points": [[0, 3], [0, -2]]
        }
    ],
    "vline_color": "#E91E63"
}

